            "Verify Integrity of Game Files",
            "<p>I see purple checkerboards, weapon or world models are missing, or experience crashes while playing a game - how can I verify that my game files are installed correctly?</p>",
            '<div class="section">  <ol>  \t<li>Restart your computer and launch <b>Steam</b></li>  <li>From a game\'s library page, select <span class="bold">Manage > Properties</span>.</li>  \t<li>Select the <b>Local files</b> tab and click the <b>Verify integrity of game files...</b> button.</li>  \t<li>Steam will verify the game\'s files - this process may take several minutes.</li>  </ol>  </div>        <div class="note">  <h3><b>Important:</b> One or more files may fail to verify.</h3>    <p>This is normal for most Steam games. The files that fail to verify are local configuration files that should not be replaced as part of this process. <span style="color: #99cc00"><b>You can safely ignore this message.</b></span></p>  </div>    <div class="warning" style="display: none;">  <h3>Warning:</h3>    <p>Do not run the verification process while performing other system-intensive processes, such as defragmenting your hard drive or scanning for viruses.</p>    <p>Do not run this process for multiple games at the same time.</p>  </div>',
