            "Required Ports for Steam",
            '<p>Which ports do I need to open on my router or firewall for Steam?</p>    <div class="section">  <h5>To log into Steam and download content:</h5>    <ul>  \t<li>HTTP (TCP remote port 80) and HTTPS (443)</li>  \t<li>UDP remote port 27015--27030</li>  \t<li>TCP remote port 27015--27030</li>  </ul>  </div>',
            '<div id="kb_ports" class="section" >    \t<div class="section" >  \t\t<h5>Steam Client</h5>  \t\t<ul>  \t\t\t<li>UDP remote port 27000--27100: Game traffic</li>  \t\t\t<li>UDP local port 27031-27036: Remote Play</li>  \t\t\t<li>TCP local port 27036: Remote Play</li>  \t\t\t<li>UDP remote port 4380</li>  \t\t</ul>  \t</div>      \t<div class="section" >  \t\t<h5>Dedicated or Listen Servers</h5>    \t\t<ul>  \t\t\t<li>TCP local port 27015 (default): SRCDS Rcon port</li>  \t\t\t<li>UDP local port 27015 (default): gameplay traffic</li>  \t\t</ul>  \t</div>    \t<div class="section" >  \t\t<h5>Steamworks P2P Networking and Steam Voice Chat</h5>  \t\t<ul>  \t\t\t<li>UDP remote port 3478</li>  \t\t\t<li>UDP remote port 4379</li>  \t\t\t<li>UDP remote port 4380</li>  \t\t</ul>  \t</div>        \t\t<div class="important">  \t\t\t<h3>Note:</h3>    \t\t\t<p>Many university networks and proxies block required ports for Steam operation - please consult your network administrator to ensure the required ports are open if you are using a university network or a proxy. <span class="bold">Ports required for Steam can not be re-mapped to HTTP or reconfigured to a custom port range.</span></p>  \t\t</div>    </div>    <div id="kb_advanced" class="section" >  \t<h4>Advanced</h4>    \t<p>For generic Steam HTTP/HTTPS requests, your proxy should allow the following domains:</p>  \t<ul>  \t\t<li>steampowered.com</li>  \t\t<li>steamcommunity.com</li>  \t\t<li>steamgames.com</li>  \t\t<li>steamusercontent.com</li>  \t\t<li>steamcontent.com</li>  \t\t<li>steamstatic.com</li>  \t\t<li>akamaihd.net</li>  \t</ul>    \t<p>Most of the non-web traffic is usually UDP but can be TCP as well. For that, the IPs will all be from the Valve network (AS32590), and a list of those IP blocks can be found here:</p>  \t<ul>  \t\t<li><a href="http://bgp.he.net/AS32590#_prefixes">IPv4</a></li>  \t\t<li><a href="http://bgp.he.net/AS32590#_prefixes6">IPv6</a></li>  \t</ul>  </div>',
