            "A Steam account already exists with that contact email address",
            '<p>When creating an account, I get the message:</p>    <p><span class="bold">A Steam account already exists with that contact email address. If you have previously created a Steam account, you should use the existing account rather than creating a new one.</span></p>  ',
            '<div class="important">  <h3>Important:</h3>    <p>This message will only display if your email address is already associated with an existing Steam account.</p>    <p>Creating a new Steam account will not allow you to register games which have already been registered.</p>  </div>    <p>Once you have created a Steam account and registered your CD Key or purchased a game on Steam, that game is permanently tied to that particular account. You can not transfer the game to a different account once you have registered it.</p>    <p>If you are attempting to access games that belong to an existing Steam account, please visit <a href="https://help.steampowered.com/">the Steam Help site</a> for assistance reclaiming your prior account.</p>    <p>&nbsp;</p>  ',
