            "The Orange Box Games Crash while Preparing to Launch",
            "<p>Team Fortress 2, Half Life 2: Episode 2, and Portal go to &quot;Preparing to launch...&quot; then quit. How can I fix this?</p>",
            '<p>Newer Source games require SSE in order to function properly. Please ensure that your processor includes SSE support.</p>  <h4>Determining SSE support</h4>  <p>CPU-Z is a free tool that can be used to determine which SSE instruction sets your CPU is capable of. Click <a href="http://www.cpuid.com/softwares/cpu-z.html">here</a> for more information.&nbsp;</p>  <p>If you are&nbsp;using&nbsp;a 32-bit operating system (64-bit systems not supported),&nbsp;the following tool can be&nbsp;used to determine which&nbsp;SSE instruction sets are supported:&nbsp;</p>  <ol>      <li>Download our <span class="bold"><a href="/downloads/9354-RTIB-6437/cputest.exe">cputest.exe</a></span> and save it to your desktop.</li>      <li>Open a command prompt.      <ul>          <li>Go to <span class="bold">Start &gt; Run</span>.</li>          <li>Type in: <tt>cmd</tt>.</li>          <li>Press <span class="bold">Enter</span>.</li>      </ul>      <p>By default, your command prompt should open to: <span class="bold">C:\\Documents and Settings\\&lt;Windows User Name&gt;</span>.</p>      </li>      <li>Type in <tt>cd desktop</tt> to change to your desktop directory and press <span class="bold">Enter</span>. Your active directory should now look like this: <span class="bold">C:\\Documents and Settings\\&lt;Windows User Name&gt;\\Desktop\\</span>.</li>      <li>To run the program, type in <tt>cputest.exe</tt> and press <span class="bold">Enter</span>. The cputest will return an analysis of your CPU that will look something like this:      <ul>          <li>          <pre>   Valve System Analyzer   ver. 0.2  Sep 27 2007     CPU Analysis   --------------------------------------------    Vendor : GenuineIntel   FuncIds : 10   Stepping:  6     Model : 15    Family :  6     Type  :  0    XModel :  0   XFamily :  0   CacheLn : 64       PN  :  No   CLFlush : Yes      MMX  : Yes      SSE  : Yes      SSE2 : Yes      SSE3 : Yes      HTT  : Yes   XVendor :   XFuncIds:  8      MMXX :  No    3DNow! :  No    3DNow!+:  No   --------------------------------------------  </pre>          </li>      </ul>      </li>      <li>Look specifically for the <span class="bold">SSE</span> section.      <p>If you see <span class="bold">SSE : No</span> then your processor does not meet the minimum system requirements to run the new Source games. You must upgrade your motherboard and/or processor in order to play these games.</p>      <p>If you see <span class="bold">SSE : Yes</span> then your processor meets the SSE support requirement of new Sources games. Please refer to the following FAQs to troubleshoot your issue:</p>      <p><a href="/kb_article.php?ref=2037-QEUH-3335">Verifying GCF Cache Files</a></p>      <p><a href="/kb_article.php?ref=7169-TIAV-5361">Troubleshooting Game Crashes</a></p>      </li>  </ol>  <p>&nbsp;</p>',
