            "1974-YFKL-4947",
            "Missing or scrambled text in Steam menus",
            "<p>My Steam application is missing text and/or the menus appear broken, how can it be fixed?</p>",
            '<h4>Windows system font</h4>  <p>This problem may&nbsp;be due to a bad or missing Windows system font. The easiest solution is to install a known good font set. Currently Steam utilizes Arial and Arial Bold fonts.</p>  <p>&nbsp;Installing Missing or Damaged Fonts</p>  <ol>      <li>Download the attached file&nbsp;by clicking the following link: <a title="SteamFonts.zip" href="downloads/1974-YFKL-4947/SteamFonts.zip">SteamFonts.zip</a></li>      <li>Log out of Steam entirely, and close all other programs that might be trying to use these fonts</li>      <li>You might also have to temporarily disable &quot;System Restore&quot; for this to work: <br />      <p>In Windows XP: Click <span class="bold">Start &gt; Control Panel</span> &gt; <span class="bold">System</span> &gt; <span class="bold">System Restore</span> &gt; then check <span class="bold">Turn off System Restore</span></p>      <p>In Windows Vista/7: Click <span class="bold">Start &gt; Control Panel &gt; System &gt; System Protection &gt; Configure &gt;</span>Click on the radio button that says <span class="bold">Turn off System Protection</span></p>      </li>      <li>After downloading the zip file use a zip utility such as <a href="http://www.winzip.com/">winzip</a> to unzip the file(s)      <p>Windows has a native unzip, just right-click on the zip and &quot;explore&quot; and drag and drop the files into a temporary directory</p>      </li>  </ol>  <h3>Windows XP</h3>  <ol>      <li>Open <span class="bold">Control Panel</span> and double click on <span class="bold">Fonts</span></li>      <li>Choose <span class="bold">File</span> and then <span class="bold">Install New Font</span></li>      <li>Finally, remember where you put the unzipped fonts and go to that directory</li>      <li>Select the font and choose \'OK\'</li>      <li>The next time you start Steam you should be able to see all the text again</li>  </ol>  <h3>Windows Vista/7</h3>  <ol>      <li>Click <span class="bold">Start &gt; Control Panel</span> and click on <span class="bold">Fonts</span></li>      <li>Remember where you put the unzipped fonts and go to that directory</li>      <li>Drag and drop the font files into the fonts directory and they should install automatically</li>      <li>The next time you start Steam you should be able to see all the text again</li>  </ol>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h4>Re-install winui.gcf</h4>  <p>The winui.gcf may periodically get corrupted.&nbsp; The main symptoms are missing text in Steam menus and the items in the My games, My media, and Tools tabs overlapping.&nbsp;</p>  <ol>      <li>Exit Steam</li>      <li>Navigate to your Steamapps folder (default location: C:\\Program Files\\Steam\\SteamApps)</li>      <li>Delete or rename the file <span class="bold">winui.gcf</span></li>      <li>Launch Steam and test the issue</li>  </ol>  <p>&nbsp;</p>',
