            '<p>Sometimes we ask that you place a Steam.cfg in a specific location to help assist with locating bugs and issues in Steam.</p>  <p>Use the following instructions to place your Steam.cfg in the correct location:</p>  <p>1. Exit Steam</p>  <p>2. Open Finder</p>  <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://support.steampowered.com/getimage.php?id=160" /></p>  <p>3. Navigate to the folder containing the Steam application (typically Applications)</p>  <p>&nbsp;<img height="108" width="132" alt="" src="https://support.steampowered.com/getimage.php?id=161" /></p>  <p>4. Right click on Steam &gt; Click on Show Package Contents</p>  <p><img height="336" width="290" alt="" src="https://support.steampowered.com/getimage.php?id=162" /></p>  <p>5. Open Contents</p>  <p><img height="91" width="304" alt="" src="https://support.steampowered.com/getimage.php?id=163" /></p>  <p>6. Open MacOS</p>  <p><img height="146" width="305" alt="" src="https://support.steampowered.com/getimage.php?id=165" /></p>  <p><img height="0" width="0" alt="" src="https://support.steampowered.com/getimage.php?id=164" /></p>  <p>7. Place the provided Steam.cfg file here</p>  <p><img height="166" width="304" alt="" src="https://support.steampowered.com/getimage.php?id=167" /></p>  <p><img height="0" width="0" alt="" src="https://support.steampowered.com/getimage.php?id=166" /></p>  <p>8. Restart Steam</p>',
