            "<p>How do I report a suspected cheater in a VAC secure game?</p>  ",
            '<div class="important">  <h3>Important:</h3>    <p>Please do not publicly post SteamIDs, Cheats or links to Cheater Websites on the forums.</p>  </div>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <h4>How do I report a suspected cheater in a VAC secure game?</h4>    <p>While it is not necessary to report cheaters playing on VAC-Secured servers - the VAC system will detect and ban these individuals - players who are suspected of cheating may be reported via the Steam Community.</p>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <div class="note">  <h3>Note:</h3>    <p>VAC does <span style="color: #ffffff"><b>not</b></span> ban based on reports. Such data is only used for tracking and statistics purposes.</p>  </div>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <h5>To report a cheater:</h5>    <ol>  \t<li>Go to the user&#39;s Steam Community profile</li>  \t<li>Click on the large More button in the upper-right corner of the user&#39;s profile</li>  \t<li>Click on the&nbsp;&quot;Report Violation&quot; button in&nbsp;this dropdown&nbsp;menu&nbsp;</li>  \t<li>Select &quot;Suspected Cheater&quot;, add a description (include the game and the name of the cheat if known), and hit &quot;Submit&quot;</li>  </ol>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <h5>To reach a user&#39;s Steam Community profile while in-game:</h5>    <ol>  \t<li>Press shift+tab (by default) to bring up the Steam Overlay</li>  \t<li>In the Friends panel on the left, click &quot;View Players&quot;</li>  \t<li>Find the offending player under the appropriate tab and click &quot;Profile&quot;</li>  </ol>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <h5>To report a cheater in Counter-Strike: Global Offensive:</h5>    <p>Reporting cheaters in Counter-Strike: Global Offensive will help identify users that should be viewed by Overwatch.</p>    <ol>  \t<li>While holding the scoreboard key (default: tab), press your alternate fire/zoom key (default: right mouse button) to show a mouse cursor.</li>  \t<li>Right-click the name on the scoreboard, and click &quot;Report&quot;.</li>  \t<li>A new dialog box will appear. Click the appropriate checkboxes and click &#39;Submit&#39;.</li>  </ol>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <h5>More information on the Valve Anti-Cheat System (VAC):</h5>    <p><a href="/kb_article.php?ref=7849-RADZ-6869" title="More information on the Valve Anti-Cheat System (VAC)">Valve Anti-Cheat System</a></p>    <p>If you are playing on an unsecured server, you may wish to report cheating to a server administrator - Steam Support cannot ban players for activities on unsecured servers.</p>    <p>&nbsp;</p>  ',
