            "Updating Linux Video Drivers",
            "<p>&nbsp;How do I update the current video driver package used by Ubuntu 12.04?</p>",
            "<p>Ubuntu's <b>Update Manager</b> automatically checks for upgrades to all installed packages on your system. However, the update schedule can differ from machine to machine.</p>  <p>To check for existing updates immediately, open <b>Update Manager</b> by either clicking the gear icon in the upper-right and selecting <b>Updates Available ... </b>or clicking the Unity symbol from the taskbar and typing &quot;update manager'&quot;. Once <b>Update Manager</b> is running, do the following:</p>  <ol>      <li>Check for updates by clicking the <b>Check </b>button.</li>      <li>Install any existing updates by clicking the <b>Install Updates</b> button.</li>      <li>Restart your machine to use the newly-installed video driver.</li>  </ol>  <p>For more information related to video drivers, see&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Valve\">https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Valve</a>.</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>",
