            "1871",
            "1609-EIPG-1853",
            "Switching Driver Packages",
            "<p>&nbsp;How do I switch to a recommended package using Ubuntu 12.04?</p>",
            '<p>Sometimes, there will be two or more packages that contain different versions of the same driver. In some cases, a newer version of a driver (installed by an earlier package) can be upgraded by installing a different package (containing the newest version of the video driver).</p>  <p>To install a specific package on your machine, do the following:</p>  <ol>      <li>Open <b>Ubuntu Software Center</b>.</li>      <li>In the search box, enter the name of the recommended package. A list of matching package names automatically appears.</li>      <li>Select the recommened package name and click the <b>Install </b>button.</li>  </ol>  <p>&nbsp;For more information on video drivers, see&nbsp;<a href="https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Valve">https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Valve</a>.</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>',
