            "Why do I have to enter a Steam Guard code every time I log in?",
            '<p>With <a href="https://support.steampowered.com/kb_article.php?ref=4020-ALZM-5519">Steam Guard</a>, Steam saves a cookie to remember your computer or browser.&nbsp;</p>    <p>If you are being repeatedly asked for a Steam Guard code on the same computer, you will need to ensure your browser has cookies enabled.</p>    <p>Additionally, please note that any of the following browser settings may keep your Steam Guard cookie and login credentials from staying stored for your next login:</p>    <ul>  \t<li>Browser security is set to &quot;high&quot;</li>  \t<li>History is auto-cleared after a short period of time</li>  \t<li>Private browsing is enabled&nbsp;</li>  </ul>',
            '<p>Your browser must have cookies enabled for <a href="https://support.steampowered.com/kb_article.php?ref=4020-ALZM-5519">Steam Guard</a> to work properly.</p>    <p>Please follow the instructions below to enable cookies and turn off other browser features that may be interfering with <a href="https://support.steampowered.com/kb_article.php?ref=4020-ALZM-5519">Steam Guard</a>:</p>    <h4>Internet Explorer</h4>    <ul>  \t<li><u><a href="https://www.thewindowsclub.com/disable-enable-cookies-internet-explorer">Enable Cookies</a></u></li>  \t<li><u><a href="http://www.thewindowsclub.com/disable-private-browsing-internet-explorer-chrome-firefox">Disable Private Browsing</a></u></li>  </ul>    <h4>​Chrome</h4>    <ul>  \t<li><u><a href="https://support.google.com/accounts/answer/61416">Enable Cookies</a></u></li>  \t<li><u><a href="http://www.thewindowsclub.com/disable-private-browsing-internet-explorer-chrome-firefox">Disable Private Browsing</a></u></li>  \t<li><u><a href="https://www.groovypost.com/howto/automatically-delete-browsing-history-chrome/">Disable Automatic Clearing of History</a></u></li>  </ul>    <h4>Safari</h4>    <ul>  \t<li><u><a href="http://www.macworld.co.uk/how-to/mac/how-enable-cookies-mac-3462635/">Enable Cookies</a></u></li>  </ul>    <h4>​Firefox</h4>    <ul>  \t<li><u><a href="https://www.whatismybrowser.com/guides/how-to-enable-cookies/firefox">Enable Cookies</a></u></li>  \t<li><u><a href="http://www.thewindowsclub.com/disable-private-browsing-internet-explorer-chrome-firefox">Disable Private Browsing</a></u></li>  \t<li><u><a href="https://www.groovypost.com/howto/automatically-delete-firefox-history-cookies-temp-exit/">Disable Automatic Clearing of History</a></u></li>  </ul>    <p>​</p>    <div class="note">  <h3>Note:</h3>    <p>Running programs including security software that clear internet history, delete other unused files, or that clean up orphaned registry entries may have a setting to clear cookies as well. Disabling this feature will prevent this issue from occurring when logging into Steam via your web browser.</p>  </div>    <p>&nbsp;</p>',
