            "Unable to log in to Steam using a web browser (Chrome, Opera, FireFox, IE)",
            "<p>I am able to log in to my Steam account using the Steam application, but when using the same username and password through a web browser, the Steam website&nbsp;indicates that my credentials are incorrect. What can I do?</p>",
            '<h3>Removing Extensions that may interfere with the login process</h3>  <p>Try disabling any browser extensions or add-ons you have installed.&nbsp;These may interfere with the login process.</p>  <p>For more information on how to remove extensions or add-ons with common browsers please visit the following links:</p>  <p>Google Chrome: <a href="http://support.google.com/chrome/bin/answer.py?hl=en&amp;answer=113907">http://support.google.com/chrome/bin/answer.py?hl=en&amp;answer=113907</a></p>  <p>Mozilla Firefox: <a href="http://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/disable-or-remove-add-ons">http://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/disable-or-remove-add-ons</a></p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h3>Attempt to log in with a different, unmodified web browser</h3>  <p>If you are unable to log into your Steam account with your current web browser, please try using a different browser and test the issue.</p>  <p>You may wish to perform a clean install of that web browser, in case any older extensions or addons may still be interfering with this process.</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>',
