            "Accessing the Desktop",
            '<p>&nbsp;<span style="font-size:13.0pt;line-height:115%;  font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;  mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA">How do I get to the desktop on SteamOS?</span></p>',
            '<p><span style="font-size:11.0pt;line-height:115%;  font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;  mso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA">To access the SteamOS desktop, it must be enabled from the Steam Settings menu. Select Settings (the gear icon in the top right) then select Interface and check the &quot;Enable access to the Linux desktop&quot; box. Now the Exit button will have an additional option, &quot;Return to Desktop&quot; that will switch to the SteamOS desktop.&nbsp;</span></p>',
