            "Disconnected by VAC: You cannot play on secure servers",
            '<div class="warning">  <p>Modifying game files and/or in-game textures may cause this error.</p>  &nbsp;    <p>Please remove any custom textures, skin changers, or software that modifies game files and restart your computer. We also recommend <a href="https://support.steampowered.com/kb_article.php?ref=2037-QEUH-3335"> verifying your game&nbsp;files</a> after making these changes.</p>  </div>    <h3>Frequently asked questions:</h3>    <ul>  \t<li><a href="#explanation">What does this error mean?</a></li>  \t<li><a href="#software">What typically causes this error?</a></li>  </ul>    <h3>How can I fix this error?</h3>    <ul>  \t<li><a href="#restart">Restart your computer</a></li>  \t<li><a href="#repair">Repair the Steam Service</a></li>  \t<li><a href="#default">Restore boot settings to default</a></li>  \t<li><a href="#files">Repair system files</a></li>  </ul>',
            '<div class="section" id="explanation">  <h3>What does this error mean?</h3>    <p>This error is caused by third party software interfering with your game or Steam. To resolve the issue, you\'ll need to disable or remove the problem software from your machine.</p>  </div>    <div class="section" id="software">  <h3>What typically causes this error?</h3>    <p>There are a number of common software conflicts that can cause this error. If you are running any of the following software, please disable it while playing:</p>    <ul>  \t<li>CCleaner</li>  \t<li>Powershell</li>  \t<li>Sandboxie</li>  \t<li>Cheat Engine</li>  \t<li>IObit Start Menu 8</li>  \t<li>Process Hacker</li>  \t<li>DLL Injectors</li>  \t<li>Hypervisors</li>  \t<li>Steam Idlers</li>  </ul>  </div>  &nbsp;    <div class="section" id="restart">  <h3>Restart your computer</h3>    <p>If the error persists on all servers it may be resolved by exiting Steam and restarting your computer.</p>  </div>    <div class="section" id="repair">  <h3>Repair the Steam Service</h3>    <p>The error may also indicate a Steam service failure. Please try repairing the Steam service:</p>    <ol>  \t<li>Exit Steam.</li>  \t<li>Click Start &gt; Run (Windows Key + R).</li>  \t<li>Type the following command: <b>&quot;C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Steam\\bin\\SteamService.exe&quot; /repair</b>  \t</li>  \t<li>Launch Steam and test the issue again.</li>  </ol>    <p><b>Note:</b> This command requires administrator privileges and may take a few minutes. If you have installed Steam to another path, please replace <b>C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Steam</b> with the correct path.</p>  </div>    <div class="section" id="default">  <h3>Restore boot settings to default</h3>    <p>Kernel integrity checks, kernel debugging, and Data Execution Prevention (DEP) must be set to default to play on VAC secured servers.</p>    <p>If you receive the following error when entering these commands they are already set to default:</p>    <ul class="nobp">  \t<li><strong>The value is protected by Secure Boot policy and cannot be modified or deleted.</strong></li>  </ul>    <p>To change boot settings to default please follow the steps below:</p>    <div class="important">  <p><b>Note:</b> If you are running Windows 8 you will need to press Windows Key + X and select Command Prompt (Admin).</p>  </div>    <ol>  \t<li>Exit Steam.</li>  \t<li>Click the Start button, then <i>All Programs</i>, and <i>Accessories</i>.</li>  \t<li>Right-click on Command Prompt and click <i>Run as administrator...</i>.</li>  \t<li>In the command prompt, type the following commands and press Enter after each command:  \t<ul class="nobp">  \t\t<li>bcdedit /deletevalue nointegritychecks</li>  \t\t<li>bcdedit /deletevalue loadoptions</li>  \t\t<li>bcdedit /debug off</li>  \t\t<li>bcdedit /deletevalue nx</li>  \t</ul>  \t</li>  \t<li>Restart your computer.</li>  \t<li>Launch Steam and test the issue again.</li>  </ol>  </div>  &nbsp;    <div class="section" id="files">  <h3>Repair system files</h3>    <p>There may be corrupt system files that are causing this issue. The following instructions will run a critical system file check on your Windows installation, replacing any missing or damaged files:</p>    <div class="important">  <p><strong>Note:</strong> If you are running Windows 8 you will need to press Windows Key + X and select Command Prompt (Admin).</p>  </div>    <ol>  \t<li>Exit Steam.</li>  \t<li>Click the Start button, <i>All Programs</i>, and <i>Accessories</i>.</li>  \t<li>Right-click on Command Prompt and click <i>Run as administrator...</i>.</li>  \t<li>In the command prompt, type the following command and press Enter:  \t<ul class="nobp">  \t\t<li>sfc /scannow</li>  \t</ul>  \t</li>  \t<li>Once the operation has completed please restart your computer, then launch Steam and test the issue again.</li>  </ol>  </div>',
