            '<p>When contacting Steam Support about a specific trade or Market transactions, it is extremely important to provide us with complete information.</p>    <p>Below are instructions on how to provide us with a screenshot of trades and market transactions:</p>    <p>This will allow you to view all previous trades, as well as item(s) included in these trades.</p>    <p><a href="https://support.steampowered.com/kb_article.php?ref=9943-WOLN-6452">Saving a Screenshot</a></p>    <div class="warning">Important: When saving a screenshot, please include the account name located on the top right corner of the page. We do not need a screenshot of any trade offers.</div>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <h4>To view your Steam Inventory History, please do the following:</h4>    <ol>  \t<li>Launch Steam</li>  \t<li>Hover over your profile name at the top and select &lsquo;Inventory&rsquo;</li>  \t<li>Click &lsquo;More&rsquo; in the top right, then &#39;View Inventory History&#39;</li>  </ol>    <p>This will allow you to view all previous trades, as well as the item(s) included in these trades.</p>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <h4>To view your Steam Market History, please do the following:</h4>    <ol>  \t<li>Launch Steam</li>  \t<li>Hover over &lsquo;Community&rsquo; in the top bar of the Steam interface and select &lsquo;Market&rsquo;</li>  \t<li>Click &lsquo;My Market History&rsquo;.</li>  </ol>    <p>This will allow you to view all previous market transactions, including any items or wallet credit involved in the transaction.</p>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <div class="note">Note: If the items that are missing were not traded to another user, please provide a complete list of the items in your ticket that you appear to be missing. Please include the last date that you know that the items were on your account.</div>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <h3>Inventory History Screenshot Example</h3>    <p><img alt="" src="https://support.steampowered.com/images/faq/4841-YKCM-0427/faq_inventory_history.png" title="Inventory History" width="100%" /></p>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <h3>Market History Screenshot Example</h3>    <p><img alt="" src="https://support.steampowered.com/images/faq/4841-YKCM-0427/MarketHistory.jpg" title="Market History" width="100%" /></p>  ',
