            "Game Character Hub",
            "<h3>Support for Game Character Hub:</h3>  <ul>  \t<li><a href='mailto:cs-row@degica.com'>Game Character Hub Support</a></li>  </ul>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <p>The community is also a great place to check out. Try these places for help from other users:</p>  <ul>  \t<li><a href='http://steamcommunity.com/app/292230/discussions'>Steam Discussions: Game Character Hub</a></li>  </ul>",
            "<h4>Issues and Fixes</h4>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h3>Verifying Your Game Files</h3>  <p>If you're encountering issues with launching or playing Game Character Hub, make sure everything installed correctly.</p>  <p>Aside from <a title='Verifying Game Cache Files (GCF)' href='kb_article.php?ref=2037-QEUH-3335'>verifying your game cache</a> and <a title='Troubleshooting Network Connectivity' href='kb_article.php?ref=1456-EUDN-2493'>checking your connection with Steam</a>, you may also need to manually run secondary installers required by this game.</p>  <p>Exit Steam entirely.</p>  <p>Reboot your computer and test the issue again. If the issue persists, you will need to contact <a href='mailto:cs-row@degica.com'>Game Character Hub Support</a>.</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h3>OS Specific Troubleshooting</h3>  <p>If the above does not resolve the issue and you are running Windows 7, Windows 8, or Windows Vista, please complete the instructions in our <a title='Windows 7, Windows 8 and Vista Troubleshooting' href='kb_article.php?ref=5688-IFHZ-2170'>Windows 7, Windows 8, and Vista Troubleshooting</a> FAQ.</p>  <p>If you are running in Windows XP, take the following steps:</p>  <ol>  \t<li>Exit Steam.</li>  \t<li>Go to the <i>Start</i> menu, select <i>Run</i>, type <i>regedit</i> and click <i>OK</i>.</li>  \t<li>Navigate to the following registry key: <tt>HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\SOFTWARE\\VALVE</tt></li>  \t<li>Right click and select <i>Permissions</i></li>  \t<li>Check the <i>Allow</i> boxes for <i>Admin</i> and <i>System</i> for both <i>Full control</i> and <i>Read</i>.</li>  </ol>  <p>&nbsp;</p>",
