            "7153-AHJV-4256",
            "How do I disable Compatibility Mode?",
            "<p>Running Steam in Windows compatibility mode is not recommended. Please follow the instructions below to remove any Windows compatibility settings so that Steam may properly function.</p>  ",
            '<div class="note">  <p>The following instructions are to be applied to both the Steam.exe as well as the steamwebhelper.exe.</p>  </div>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <ol>  \t<li>Browse to your Steam installation (Usually C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Steam\\)</li>  \t<li>Right click on Steam.exe (or bin\\steamwebhelper.exe), choose <i>Properties</i></li>  \t<li>Click on the <i>Compatibility</i> tab</li>  \t<li>Uncheck any boxes that are checked, and click Apply</li>  \t<li>Then, click the &quot;Show settings for all users&quot; button</li>  \t<li>Again, make sure none of these boxes are checked, and click <i>Ok</i></li>  \t<li>Click <i>Ok</i> to close any open dialog boxes.</li>  \t<li>Double click on Steam.exe to launch Steam.</li>  \t<li>Re-test the issue.</li>  </ol>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <div class="important">  <ul>  \t<li>The default location for the Steam.exe file is C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Steam\\</li>  \t<li>The default location for the steamwebhelper.exe file is C:\\Program Files (x86)\\Steam\\bin\\.</li>  </ul>  </div>  ',
