            '<!DOCTYPE html>  <html>  <head>  \t<title>Valve Index Orders</title>  </head>    <body>    <div class="container">  \t<img src="https://support.steampowered.com/steamvr/FitGuide/GuideHeader.png" style="width:100%;height:242px;">  \t<div class="bottom-left"><h1 class="page-title">Valve Index Orders</h1></div>  \t<div class="bottom-right"><a href="https://support.steampowered.com/kb_cat.php?id=106" style="color: white">&lt; Back to Support</a></div>  </div>    <div class="content-section">    \t<h4>How does the order system work?</h4>  \t\t<p>When you submit an order for Index hardware, an estimated shipping window is calculated. Steam will email you with an update at the following times:</p>  \t\t<ul>  \t\t<li>When your order is received.</li>  \t\t<li>When your hardware is ready to ship and requires payment.</li>  \t\t<li>When we\'ve confirmed your shipping address and finalized your payment.</li>  \t\t<li>When your tracking information is available.</li>  \t\t</ul>  \t\t<p>You can only complete the purchase from the Steam account that placed the order. Orders are fulfilled in the order they are received. Your order is not final until payment is received.</p>    \t\t<h4>How do I check my order status?</h4>  \t\t\t<p>You can view the status of an order at any time by visiting <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/account/history/">your purchase history</a>.</p>  \t\t\t<p>Any orders appearing in the "In-process" have been received but are pending. You will be invited to complete your order at a later time.</p>  \t\t\t<p>If your order has been completed, it will appear in your transaction history instead. You can click "view shipment details" to see the current status of your order.  \t\t\t<ul>  \t\t\t<li>If your order status is "processing", then your payment is complete and your order is being processed at our warehouse.</li>  \t\t\t<li>If your order status is "ready to ship", then your order has been allocated and will ship soon, usually within 2-3 business days.</li>  \t\t\t<li>If your order status is "shipped", then your order is on its way!</li>  \t\t\t</ul>    \t<h4>When do I pay?</h4>  \t\t<p>Payment and shipping information are currently only requested when your hardware is ready to ship. If you see a green payment button on your order, it is ready for purchase. If you see an estimated shipment window only, you will be invited to complete your purchase closer to that time.</p>  \t\t<p>Your order is considered pending until we have confirmed your shipping address and finalized your payment.</p>    \t<h4>Can I order more than one item?</h4>  \t\t<p>Each account can have one active order for each available store package. For example, you can place separate orders for both an Index Headset and a VR Kit.</p>    \t<h4>Question about shipping?</h4>  \t\t<p>Check out our <a href="https://support.steampowered.com/kb_article.php?ref=7077-YUOA-2321">Hardware Shipping FAQ</a>.</p>    \t<h4>Questions about Half-Life: Alyx and bonus content?</h4>  \t\t<p>Check out our <a href="https://support.steampowered.com/kb_article.php?ref=8882-AKCV-6791">Half-Life: Alyx FAQ</a>.</p>    </div>  </body>    <style class="Index-reservations-css" type="text/css">    \t.right_col {  \t\tdisplay: none;  \t}    \t.left_col {  \t\twidth: 100%;  \t}    \t#content {  \t\tfont-family: "Motiva Sans Light", "Motiva Sans", Arial, Tahoma, sans-serif;  \t\t-moz-box-sizing: border-box;  \t\tbox-sizing: border-box;  \t}    \t#content .pagetext {  \t\tpadding: 13px 13px 0;  \t\tbackground: none;  \t}    \t#content #question .content-section {  \t\tbackground: #202020;    \t}    \t#content #question .black-section {  \t\tbackground: #000000;  \t\tpadding: 13px 13px 0;  \t}    \t#question {  \t\tborder-top: none;  \t\tmargin-bottom: 0px;  \t\tnone repeat scroll 0 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);  \t}    \t#question > h1:first-child {  \t\tdisplay: none;  \t}    \t#wrapper {  \t\t  background: black;  \t}    \t.content-section {          position: relative;    \t\tpadding: 13px;  \t\tbackground: none repeat scroll 0 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);  \t\tmargin-bottom: 0px;  \t\tz-index: 999;  \t}    \t.content-section img {  \t\tdisplay: block;  \t\tmargin: 20px auto 0;  \t}    \th1 {  \t\tfont-size: 2.5em;  \t}    \th4 {  \t\tColor: #DA70D6;  \t}    \tsup {  \t    vertical-align: top;  \t    font-size: smaller;  \t}    \t.topic-description-container {  \t\tfont-size: 16px;  \t}    \t.topic-header-text {  \t\tmargin-bottom: 10px;  \t}    \t.nav-container-float{  \t\twidth: 50%;  \t\tfloat: left;  \t\tcolor: #67c1f5;  \t\tfont-weight: bold;  \t}    \t.clear-float {  \t\tclear: both;  \t\theight: 0;  \t\tcontent: hidden;  \t}    \thtml {  \t\tmin-height: 100%;  \t    margin: 0;  \t}    \tbody {  \t\tmin-height: 100%;  \t    margin: 0;  \t\tbackground-color: black;  \t}    \t.horiz-rule {  \t\theight: 1px;  \t\twidth: 100%;  \t\tborder-top: 1px solid #fff;  \t\tmargin: 25px 0;  \t}    \t.column {  \t  float: left;  \t}    \t.left {  \t  width: 20%;  \t  margin: 0 auto;  \t  padding: 30px  \t}    \t.right {  \t  width: 80%;  \t}    \t.half {  \t  width: 40%;  \t}    \t.row:after {  \t  content: "";  \t  display: table;  \t  clear: both;  \t}    \t.container {  \t\tposition: relative;  \t\tcolor: white;  \t}    \t.bottom-left {  \t  position: absolute;  \t  bottom: 8px;  \t  left: 16px;  \t  vertical-align: top;  \t}    \t.bottom-right {  \t  position: absolute;  \t  bottom: 8px;  \t  right: 16px;  \t  z-index: 999;  \t}    </style>      </html>  ',
