            '<h1 class="page-title">Windows Mixed Reality and SteamVR</h1>  \t<p>Windows Mixed Reality is Microsoft\'s hardware and software platform for augmented and virtual reality experiences. The current generation of Mixed Reality Headsets are available from Acer, Dell, HP, Lenovo and Samsung.</p>  \t  <h4>First Steps</h4>  \t<h5>Set up your Windows Mixed Reality Device:</h5>   \t    <p>If you haven’t already, make sure that you have installed both the <a href="https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/mixed-reality/immersive_headset_setup">Windows Mixed Reality Headset</a> and the <a href="https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/mixed-reality/install_windows_mixed_reality">Windows Mixed Reality Portal.</a></p>\t    \t<h5>Make sure your system meets the requirements:</h5>   \t\t<p>The <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4039260/windows-10-mixed-reality-pc-hardware-guidelines">requirements for Windows Mixed Reality headsets</a> may differ from those of SteamVR. </p>  \t\t<div class="warning-box">  \t\t\t<p>PC requirements vary for available apps & content on Steam. Please see the minimum requirements per title. Additionally we\'ve found that running SteamVR on a PC with a GTX 1070 video card (or equivalent) and an Intel Core i7 processor on the latest version of Windows works well with a broad range of SteamVR applications.</p>  \t\t\t<p>If your PC does not meet these specs you won\'t be blocked from running Windows Mixed Reality for SteamVR however this may impact the performance and quality of the overall experience.</p>  \t\t</div>  \t\t<p>You can also use the <a href="http://store.steampowered.com/app/323910/SteamVR_Performance_Test/">SteamVR performance test</a> to see if your system is SteamVR ready.</p>                                      <h4><a href="https://steamcdn-a.akamaihd.net/client/installer/SteamWindowsMRInstaller.exe">Download the installer</a> for SteamVR and Windows Mixed Reality</h4>  \t<ol>  \t\t<li>Run the installer and create an account.</li>  \t\t<li>Launch <a href="steam://run/250820">SteamVR</a> when ready to begin the tutorial.</li>  \t</ol>    <h4>Button Mapping</h4>  \t<p>For some quick button mapping information, see our diagram below. Otherwise head over <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4040517/windows-10-controllers-windows-mixed-reality">Windows Mixed Reality controllers page</a> for more information.</p>    <div align="center">  <br>  <img src="https://support.steampowered.com/images/faq/steam_vr/winmr_controller.png?v=valveisgoodatcaching" width="75%" height="75%">  <br>  </div>    <div align="center" class="note"><h1>Still have Questions?</h1></div>\t    <h5>What headset should I choose?</h5>  \t<p>There are several Microsoft Windows Mixed Reality headsets to choose from, and all will work with SteamVR. You can learn more about available hardware <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/windows-mixed-reality">here.</a></p>\t  \t  <h5>What games on Steam work with Windows Mixed Reality?</h5>  \t<p>Compatible titles will have "Windows Mixed Reality" under "VR Support." Check the right-side of any game page to find out more details about compatibility (controllers, room-scale, etc)</p>  \t<p>To find out if any title works with your headset on Steam, look for the "Windows Mixed Reality" label under VR Support. Other titles may also work with Windows Mixed Reality even if they haven\'t been specifically labeled by the developer.</p>    <h5>How do I report issues with Windows Mixed Reality?</h5>  \t<p>For issues related to Windows Mixed Reality on Steam, please <a href="https://help.steampowered.com/en/wizard/HelpWithGame/?appid=250820">contact support</a>\ufeff or visit the <a href="https://steamcommunity.com/app/250820">SteamVR Community Hub\ufeff.</a></p>  \t\t  <p>  <style class="steam-shipping-css" type="text/css">html {  \t\tbox-sizing: border-box;  \t}  \t  \tp {  \t\tfont-size: 14px;  \t\tline-height: 24px;  \t}    \tp span {  \t\tcolor: #fff;  \t}    \tul > li {  \t\tpadding: 0;  \t}    \th4 {  \t\tfont-size: 20px;  \t}    \t.right_col {  \t\tdisplay: none;  \t}    \t.left_col {  \t\twidth: 100%;  \t}    \t#content {  \t\tfont-family: "Motiva Sans Light", "Motiva Sans", Arial, Tahoma, sans-serif  \t}    \t#content .pagetext {  \t\tpadding: 13px 13px 0;  \t\tbackground: none;  \t}    \t#question {  \t\tborder-top: none;  \t\tmargin-bottom: 0px;  \t\tnone repeat scroll 0 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);  \t}    \t#question > h1:first-child {  \t\tdisplay: none;  \t}    \t.page-title {  \t\tfont-size: 1.7em;  \t\tfont-weight: normal;  \t\tmargin: 0 0 10px;  \t\tpadding: 0;  \t\tfont-family: "Motiva Sans", Arial, sans-serif;  \t}    \t.content-section,  \t.content-hover-section {  \t\tbackground: none repeat scroll 0 0 rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);  \t\tmargin-bottom: 10px;  \t}    \t.content-section {  \t\tpadding: 13px;  \t}    \t.content-hover-section {  \t\toverflow: auto;  \t}    \t.content-hover-section:hover {  \t\tbackground: #015B8F;  \t}    \t.active {  \t\tbackground: #015B8F;  \t\tcolor: #fff;  \t}    \t.content-section img {  \t\ttext-align: center;  \t}    \t#question .content-section {  \t\tmargin-bottom: 0;  \t}    \t.left_col .pagetext .notice-text {  \t\tfont-size: 18px;  \t\tpadding-top: 20px;  \t}  \t  \tul {    \t\tpadding-left: 15px;  \t}  \t  \tol {    \t\tpadding-left: 15px;  \t}  \t  \timg {      max-width: 100%;      height: auto;  \tdisplay: block;      margin-left: auto;      margin-right: auto;  \t  \t}    \t.sublist {  \t\tmargin-top: 8px;  \t}    \t.row:after {  \t    content: "";  \t    display: table;  \t    clear: both;  \t}  \t  \t.bgimg {      background-image: url("https://support.steampowered.com/images/faq/steam_vr/BaseStation2.0/BGimage.png");  \tbackground-repeat: repeat-y;  }  \t  </style>  </p>    <script type="text/javascript">  \t  var headerImage = $("<img/>", {  \t\t\tsrc: "https://support.steampowered.com/images/faq/steam_vr/vive_install/SteamVR_Support_Header_Main.png",  \t\t\tcss: {height: "320px", width: "100%"},  \t\t});    \t\t$(".container").css({"background": "url(https://support.steampowered.com/images/faq/steam_universe/bg.jpg) 0px 0px / 100% 6000px no-repeat", "width": "950px", "display": "inline-block"});  \t\t$("#contain_nav_search").after(headerImage);    \t\t// hack for hiding deskpro p tag around style  \t\t$(".steam-rma-css").parent("p").css("display", "none")    \t\t$("document").ready( function () {  \t\t\t$("#question").hide();      \t\t\t$(".troubleshooting_header_container").click(function (event) {  \t\t\t\tevent.preventDefault();  \t\t\t\treturn debounce(dropDownCollapse(this), 400 );  \t\t\t});    \t\t\tfunction dropDownCollapse (targetEl) {  \t\t\t\tvar $container = $(targetEl).closest(".content-hover-section");  \t\t\t\t$container.toggleClass("active");  \t\t\t\t$container.find(".troubleshooting-collapse").toggleClass("collapse");  \t\t\t\t$container.find(".triangle-toggle").toggleClass("collapse-triangle");  \t\t\t}    \t\t\tfunction debounce(func, wait, immediate) {  \t\t\t\tvar timeout;  \t\t\t\treturn function() {  \t\t\t\t\tvar context = this, args = arguments;  \t\t\t\t\tvar later = function() {  \t\t\t\t\t\ttimeout = null;  \t\t\t\t\t\tif (!immediate) func.apply(context, args);  \t\t\t\t\t};  \t\t\t\t\tvar callNow = immediate && !timeout;  \t\t\t\t\tclearTimeout(timeout);  \t\t\t\t\ttimeout = setTimeout(later, wait);  \t\t\t\t\tif (callNow) func.apply(context, args);  \t\t\t\t};  \t\t\t};  \t\t  \t\t});  \t  </script>',
