            '<link href="https://cdn.steamstatic.com/apps/dota2/css/deskpro_kb_no_col.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />  <p style="text-align: center;"><b>​<img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_pugna_head.jpg" style="width: 246px; height: 200px;" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size:16px;">​​</span></span>&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_life_stealer_face.jpg" style="width: 163px; height: 200px;" />&nbsp; &nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_pudge.jpg" style="width: 232px; height: 200px;" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_clinkz.jpg" style="width: 193px; height: 200px;" /></b></p>  ',
            '<ul>  \t<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">We occasionally need to request&nbsp;alternate low-violence versions of some workshop items with some or all of the following changes:</span></span>  \t<ul>  \t\t<li><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Replace or remove human skulls and some types of bones</span></span></li>  \t\t<li><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Replace or remove excessive&nbsp;wounds or entrails</span></span></li>  \t\t<li><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">Darken or remove bright red blood</span></span></li>  \t</ul>  \t</li>  \t<li style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6px;">If low violence alternates are requested, they should be submitted to the workshop as new &quot;low-violence&quot; submissions instead of replacing existing submissions.</span></font></li>  \t<li style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6px;">If you prepare a low-violence item, it will preview on the regular hero base model in the workshop tool, it is&nbsp;not possible to preview items on a low-violence hero base model. </span></font></li>  \t<li style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6px;">Some workshop reference files available through the <a href="http://www.dota2.com/workshop/requirements">Hero Resource</a> pages include low-violence models, textures or images. Low-violence files&nbsp;will have an &quot;lv&quot; in the file name.</span></font></li>  </ul>    <p style="text-align: center;"><b><img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_file.JPG" /></b></p>    <ul>  \t<li style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6px;">If you have excessive blood on items, it will be helpful to keep the blood on a separate layer in your texture source file so that it will be easy to darken or remove the blood if this is requested.</span></font></li>  </ul>    <p><font face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6px;">​</span></font></p>    <hr />  <p>&nbsp;</p>    <p><font face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6px;">Below are&nbsp;alternate low-violence textures and models Valve created&nbsp;for some Dota heroes:</span></font></p>    <p>&nbsp;</p>    <h2><strong><font face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6px;">Life Stealer, Bane and Clinkz</span></font></strong></h2>    <ul>  \t<li><font face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6px;">These heroes have a different model and different textures</span></font></li>  </ul>    <p style="text-align: center;"><b><img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_life_stealer.jpg" style="width: 265px; height: 250px;" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_life_stealer_face.jpg" style="width: 203px; height: 250px;" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_life_stealer_back.jpg" style="width: 294px; height: 250px;" /></b></p>    <p style="text-align: center;"><b><img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_bane.jpg" style="width: 250px; height: 250px;" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_clinkz_head.jpg" style="width: 300px; height: 250px;" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_clinkz.jpg" style="width: 241px; height: 250px;" /></b></p>    <h2>&nbsp;</h2>    <h2><strong><font face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6px;">Pudge</span></font></strong></h2>    <ul>  \t<li style="text-align: justify;"><font face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6px;">Pudge has the same model but altered wound details and darkened blood on textures, including darkened blood on the base right hand that may need matching darkened&nbsp;blood on low-violence left hand items:</span></font></li>  </ul>    <p style="text-align: center;"><b><img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_pudge.jpg" style="width: 290px; height: 250px;" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_pudge_belly.jpg" style="width: 264px; height: 250px;" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_pudge2_armleft_color.jpg" style="width: 250px; height: 250px;" /></b></p>    <h2>&nbsp;</h2>    <h2><strong><font face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6px;">Lone Druid and Witch Doctor</span></font></strong></h2>    <ul>  \t<li><font face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6px;">These heroes have human skull ornaments&nbsp;replaced or removed from their items:</span></font></li>  </ul>    <p style="text-align: center;"><b><img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_lone_druid_crop.jpg" style="width: 271px; height: 250px;" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_witchdoctor_crop.jpg" style="width: 276px; height: 250px;" />&nbsp;&nbsp;</b></p>    <h2>&nbsp;</h2>    <h2><strong><font face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6px;">Doom, Pugna,&nbsp;Lich, and&nbsp;Shadow Demon</span></font></strong></h2>    <ul>  \t<li><font face="arial, helvetica, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 25.6px;">The skull-like lower faces of these heroes are covered for low-violence:</span></font></li>  </ul>    <p style="text-align: center;"><b><img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_doom_head.JPG" style="width: 179px; height: 150px;" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_pugna_head.jpg" style="width: 185px; height: 150px;" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_lich_head.jpg" style="width: 174px; height: 150px;" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="http://cdn.dota2.com/apps/dota2/images/workshop/guidelines/low_violence/lv_shadow_demon_head.jpg" style="width: 213px; height: 150px;" /></b></p>    <p style="text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>    <p><span style="font-size:16px;"><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><a href="http://www.dota2.com/workshop/">Dota 2 Item Workshop&nbsp;Guidelines Homepage</a></span></span></p>  ',
